creator: John Hay;  John George Nicolay
description:
LibriVox recording of Abraham Lincoln: A History (Volume 2) by John Hay; John George Nicolay.
Read in English by Denise Nordell; Margaret Espaillat; Jim Caroompas; Shelly Tumbleson; im Simpl; Veronica Jenkins; JudyDerby; Sheila; Amabam; MaryAnnS; Lazlo; Gary Davis; Michele Fry
Abraham Lincoln: A History is an 1890 ten-volume account of the life and times of Abraham Lincoln, written by John Nicolay and John Hay, who were his personal secretaries during the American Civil War. Volume 2 chronicles Lincoln's life from 1856-1860. - Summary adapted from wikipedia by Ann Boulais
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
